title.text: BULK PROCESSING OF TEXT ON A MASSIVELY PARALLEL COMPUTER

entities.text: TEXT ON A MASSIVELY PARALLEL COMPUTER

abstractContent.text: Dictionary lookup is a computational activity that can be greatly accelerated when performed on large amounts of text by a parallel computer such as the Connection Machine TM Computer (CM).
Several algorithms for parallel dictionary lookup are discussed, including one that allows the CM to lookup words at a rate 450 times that of lookup on a Symbolics 3600 Lisp Machine.
